"Looks like there's a problem with your router. Here's what you can do:
"1. Issues with public WLAN networks" There might be too many people connected to this network at the moment, or the network is experiencing technical issues. Connect to a different network or use mobile data instead.
"2.Insufficient balance" Overdue payments might block your access to wireless networks. Contact your service provider to solve this problem.
"3. Issues with router settings" Reboot your router. Also check whether the issue you've encountered is described in the instruction manual that came with it.
"4. Issues with the router" Your router might be not working properly. Reset your router (you can check how to do it in the instruction manual that came with it).
"5. Hardware issues" Your router might not be connected to the internet. Check whether the network cable is connected properly."
